==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oversell
<hw>O`ver*sell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Oversold</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overselling</conjf>. ]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sell
for a higher price than; to exceed in selling price.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One whose beauty⟦br⟧
Would <qex>oversell</qex> all Italy.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To sell beyond means of delivery.</def>
<mark>[Brokers' Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oversold market</b></col> <fld>(Brokers' Cant)</fld>,
<cd>a market in which stocks or commodities have been sold
⟦ldquo⟧short⟦rdquo⟧ to such an extent that it is difficult to obtain
them for delivery.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overset</ent>⟦br⟧
